4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING TAX APPEAL PROCEDURE LAWS; PROVIDING FOR
5 INFORMAL REVIEW OF RESIDENTIAL PROPERTY TAX DISPUTES AT THE MONTANA TAX APPEAL
6 BOARD; PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; AMENDING SECTION 15-2-301, MCA; AND PROVIDING
7 AN APPLICABILITY DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 15-2-301, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "15-2-301. Appeal of county tax appeal board decisions -- RULEMAKING. (1) (a) The county tax
13 appeal board shall mail a copy of its decision to the taxpayer and to the property assessment division of the
14 department of revenue.
15 (b) If the appearance provisions of 15-15-103 have been complied with, a person or the
16 department on behalf of the state or any municipal corporation aggrieved by the action of the county tax appeal
17 board may appeal to the Montana tax appeal board by filing with the Montana board a notice of appeal within
18 30 calendar days after the receipt of the decision of the county board. The notice must specify the action
19 complained of and the reasons assigned for the complaint.
20 (c) Notice of acceptance of an appeal must be given to the county board by the Montana board.
21 (d) The Montana board shall set the appeal for hearing either in its office in the capital or at the
22 county seat as the Montana board considers advisable to facilitate the performance of its duties or to
23 accommodate parties in interest.
24 (e) The Montana board shall give to the appellant and to the respondent at least 15 calendar days'
25 notice of the time and place of the hearing.
26 (2) (a) At the time of giving notice of acceptance of an appeal, the Montana board may require the
27 county board to certify to it the minutes of the proceedings resulting in the action and all testimony taken in
28 connection with its proceedings.
