1 (5) Except as provided in subsection (2)(c) regarding industrial property, in connection with any
2 appeal under this section, the Montana board is not bound by common law and statutory rules of evidence or
3 rules of discovery and may affirm, reverse, or modify any decision. To the extent that this section is in conflict
4 with the Montana Administrative Procedure Act, this section supersedes that act. The Montana board may not
5 amend or repeal any administrative rule of the department. The Montana board shall give an administrative rule
6 full effect unless the Montana board finds a rule arbitrary, capricious, or otherwise unlawful.
7 (6) The decision of the Montana board is final and binding on all interested parties and not subject
8 to a rehearing unless reversed or modified by judicial review. Proceedings for judicial review of a decision of the
9 Montana board under this section are subject to the provisions of 15-2-303 and the Montana Administrative
10 Procedure Act to the extent that it does not conflict with 15-2-303.
11 (7) Sections 15-6-134 and 15-7-111 may not be construed to prevent the department from
12 implementing an order to change the valuation of property.
13 (8) If the appeal involves class four residential property, a person satisfying the requirements in
14 subsection (1)(b) may make an election to have the Montana board consider the appeal on an informal basis. If
15 an informal review is elected, the decision of the Montana board is final and binding on all parties, INCLUDING
16 THE DEPARTMENT, and is not subject to reconsideration or an appeal to district court BY THE TAXPAYER OR THE
17 DEPARTMENT. THE MONTANA BOARD SHALL ADOPT RULES OUTLINING INFORMAL REVIEW PROCEDURES PURSUANT TO
18 THIS SUBSECTION."
19
20 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Applicability. [This act] applies to Montana tax appeal board
21 proceedings filed on or after [the effective date of this act].
